 ## Changelog rule

-Each meaningful research wave gets a [CHANGELOG.md](CHANGELOG.md) entry with:
+Each empirical research wave — one that produces a REVISE / GO / STOP
+transition or moves the empirical-state ledger — gets a
+[CHANGELOG.md](CHANGELOG.md) entry with:

 - empirical state (REVISE / GO / STOP, or no-change with reason)
 - α / β / γ / C_Σ if measured, or "pending — coh unavailable" if not
 - bottleneck axis (which of α / β / γ is weakest)
 - coherence delta (what moved since the prior entry)
 - what changed (file-level summary, not commit summary)
 - what remains unproven
 - next gate (the next condition that must be met)

 The changelog is a coherence ledger, not a release-note style log. It
 records whether the research project still describes one system, not which
 features shipped.
+
+Coherence-only waves (drift sweeps, doc reconciliation, protocol-internal
+refactors that do not move empirical state) do not produce CHANGELOG
+entries. Their record lives in `.cdd/waves/<wave>/wave-closeout.md` and
+`.cdd/iterations/`. The CHANGELOG is for empirical transitions; coherence
+work is traced in its own ledger surfaces.
